The paper focuses on using active perception to accomplish manipulation tasks in robotics, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The use of cameras and visual perception also suggests computer vision (cs.CV) as a likely sub-category. The paper also mentions reinforcement learning and self-supervised learning, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI). Finally, the application of these techniques to control a robotic system suggests the sub-category of control systems (cs.SY) as a possibility.
